<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="214" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,150,608]" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,150,176]" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterolateral margin of pronotum with solid black stripe reaching all or part of its extension with remaining part smoky black and narrower than solid part. Anterolateral margin punctured dorsally. Cicatrices of pronotum with dark brown punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
<figureCitation box="[854,959,222,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="31.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[241,1344,194,1910]" captionTargetId="figure-20@31.[226,1361,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURE 20. Dorsal and ventral view. H. runcinatus sp. n. A–B; H. similis sp. n. C–D; H. trilobulatus sp. n. E–F; H. unguiculatus sp. n. G–H; H. ventrotuberculatus sp. n. I–J (Scale = 5mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777100" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777100/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Fig. 20G</figureCitation>
). Male (
<figureCitation box="[1049,1188,222,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[175,1407,640,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-123@26.[160,1427,626,1938]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 16. Hypoxys unguiculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777092/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Fig. 16A–D</figureCitation>
). Pygophore with dorsal rim concave (
<figureCitation box="[338,441,258,284]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[175,1407,640,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-123@26.[160,1427,626,1938]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 16. Hypoxys unguiculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777092/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Fig. 16A</figureCitation>
). Superior process of genital cup subtriagular with distal part acuminated and anterior part bifid; adjacent to dorsal rim; visible in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[731,868,294,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[175,1407,640,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-123@26.[160,1427,626,1938]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 16. Hypoxys unguiculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777092/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Fig. 16A–C</figureCitation>
). Paramere with anterior lobe short and rounded to truncate, distal lobe large and rounded; margin black; inner carina ending at the posterior lobe. Proctiger with dorsolateral tuft of long setae, dorsal ridge setose (
<figureCitation box="[655,794,366,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[175,1407,640,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-123@26.[160,1427,626,1938]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 16. Hypoxys unguiculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777092/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Fig. 16A–D</figureCitation>
); posterior face pentagonal, base of tufts of setae swollen (
<figureCitation box="[159,297,402,428]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[175,1407,640,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-123@26.[160,1427,626,1938]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 16. Hypoxys unguiculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777092/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Fig. 16B–C</figureCitation>
). Ventral rim with medial excavation widely open; expansions long and rounded, clearly surpassing level of posterolateral angles in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[659,762,438,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="26.[151,250,1961,1985]" captionTargetBox="[175,1407,640,1919]" captionTargetId="figure-123@26.[160,1427,626,1938]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 16. Hypoxys unguiculatus sp. n. A–D Male, pygophore; A—dorsal view; B—posterior view; C—lateroposterior view; D—ventral view (Scale = 1mm)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6777092" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6777092/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="214">Fig. 16D</figureCitation>
). Ventral surface with several large dark spots and punctured spots adjacent to midline. Female unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
